33. cicatricum et scelerie. The expression is of the nature of what grammarians call hendiadys. In prose the ideas would be grouped more logically. The real object of the feeling of ‘shame’ is one, viz. the ‘guilt’ of civil war; the ‘scars' are only its memorials, the ‘brotherhood’ of the combatants its aggravation. 39. diffingas. The verb ‘ diffingere' is found in no other author, and in Horace only here and in Od. 3. 29. 47 ‘neque Diffinget infectumque reddet.' The Scholiasts interpret it here ‘ refabricare,’ ‘reformare,' there ‘ immutare) It seems to mean ‘to make differ· ’ ently,' i. e. (in this case) ‘ to a different purpose.'
